description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within Cardiff and Vale UHB for an Office Manager to join the Community Nutrition and Dietetic team. We are looking for a dynamic and innovative administrator with extensive skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the supervision and delivery of the administration function within the community dietetic service. This will include waiting list management, validation, booking processes and gathering data. The post holder will supervise a team of administrative staff within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will support your Continuous Professional Development in line with your KSF outline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for someone who shares our values that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We trust one another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We respect each other&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We take personal responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We treat people with kindness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We act with integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders will be expected at all times to behave in accordance with our values demonstrating commitment to the delivery of high quality services to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Fiona Moore Job title Dietetic Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address fiona.moore@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 02920668089&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;other contact Helen nicholls helen.nicholls2@wales.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
